# UIUX.Web — clawbot deploy (detail)

**Hard rule (summary):** [`clawbot-ui-deployment-complete.mdc`](clawbot-ui-deployment-complete.mdc) — **alwaysApply.** UI changes are **not** complete without pull, correct verification path, restart when needed, and browser proof.

## `web` rebuild vs `dashboard.html`

`UIUX.Web/Dockerfile` **COPY**s `dashboard.html`, `styles.css`, etc. into **`web`’s** `/usr/share/nginx/html/`. **`nginx/default.conf`** proxies **`/dashboard.html`** (and `/dashboard`) to **`api`**, which reads **`/repo/UIUX.Web/dashboard.html`** from the **`api`** mount. So:

- **Operator dashboard at `/dashboard.html`:** after **`git pull`**, the live document is the file on the **`api`** repo mount — **do not** use **`web`’s** baked copy as proof.
- **Rebuild `web`** when you change assets nginx serves **without** proxying (e.g. `index.html`, `styles.css`, `app.js` by direct path).

The **`api`** service mounts **`../:/repo`** — Python changes under `modules/` need **restart `api`** (cached imports). **`dashboard.html`** content is read from disk per request in **`api_server`**; no restart needed for HTML-only edits to that file.

## Commands (clawbot)

```bash
ssh jmiller@clawbot.a51.corp
cd ~/blackbox && git fetch origin main && git pull origin main && git rev-parse HEAD
cd ~/blackbox/UIUX.Web && docker compose build web && docker compose up -d web api
```

Verify **`dashboard.html`** (what the browser gets at `/dashboard.html`):

```bash
cd ~/blackbox/UIUX.Web && docker compose exec api grep -q 'tc-scorecard-block' /repo/UIUX.Web/dashboard.html && echo OK
# or: curl -sk https://127.0.0.1/dashboard.html | head -30
```

(Using **`web`’s** `/usr/share/nginx/html/dashboard.html` is **not** valid proof for that URL — nginx proxies to **api**.)

Operator URL (see `docker-compose.yml` / site): typically HTTPS on host; **hard refresh** after deploy.

## Do not claim “live for operator” without

Successful **pull**, **`build web`**, **up -d**, **in-container grep/curl**, and **browser confirmation** (or explicit operator sign-off).

